Fix JavaScript null exception on dialog title (#28)

This commit resolves a null exception in 'baseDialogExtensionHandler.js' and 'mudBlazorExtensions.all.js'. The issue was occurring when 'dialogTitleEl' was null and we were trying to access innerText property of it. Now, we ensure 'dialogTitleEl' is not null before accessing its property, thus, preventing the null exception. Minor formatting changes have also been made in '.DotSettings.user'.

Update theme editing functionality in MudBlazor

In MudExThemeEdit.razor.cs, changed the event callback parameters to incorporate 'ThemeChangedArgs'. Loading function refactored to optimise state changes. Also made readability enhancements across various .razor files. All alterations aimed at improving the theme editing functionality and providing better clarity in terms of project structuring and code logic.

Update codebase to newer package versions and refine function parameters

Updated MudBlazor to version 6.7.0 and various other packages to their latest versions in the MainSample.MAUI.Moana.csproj, MudBlazor.Extensions.csproj, and MainSample.WebAssembly.csproj files. These upgrades maintain the project's compatibility with the latest software.

Additionally, extraneous parameters were removed in the DialogService.cs and DialogService.FileDisplay.cs files to streamline the function calls. In MudExIconPicker.razor.cs, the Available property was repurposed from Css Variables to represent Available Icons with automatic filling from IconTypes, enhancing clarity in code purpose. Lastly, corresponding changes were made in the documentation file MudBlazor.Extensions.xml.
